				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T10:54:21.881664-04:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:26:02.603722-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "PTSPiGX+RB2KdcVi8iPh/g=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Some pink plane implementations try to mitigate the burden of account hierarchies by bolting on a concept to represent dimensions/aspects of transactions not inherent to their account designation. These can be generic \"tags\" or \"classes\", or more specific, like \"projects\". These offer flexibility to the user, and, to the extent they are first-class domain objects, more power. However, in practice this seems to result in a Frankensteinian hybrid, where users arbitrarily assign certain aspects to accounts, and others to secondary dimensions, without clear value-based rules."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:41:11.982693-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:41:11.982693-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "SbsVZ+eVRcqTo+WRmprsCA=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "A distinct account should exist when the distinction changes something about how an amount behaves financially:\nit carries a balance that must be reconciled;\nit is an asset, liability, equity, income, or expense;\nrecognition occurs at a different time;\nit is depreciated or amortized;\nit has different normal debit/credit behavior;\nexternal accounting or tax reporting requires a stable posting distinction;\ndifferent posting, approval, or control rules apply."
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [
									{
										"__type" : "textSnippet",
										"children" : {
											"__type" : "snippets",
											"items" : [ ]
										},
										"createEmail" : {
											"__type" : "email",
											"emailString" : "<unknown>"
										},
										"createTime" : {
											"__type" : "time",
											"time" : {
												"__type" : "dateAndTime",
												"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:44:29.648639-04:00"
											}
										},
										"editEmail" : {
											"__type" : "email",
											"emailString" : "<unknown>"
										},
										"editTime" : {
											"__type" : "time",
											"time" : {
												"__type" : "dateAndTime",
												"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T12:52:25.096123-04:00"
											}
										},
										"uid" : {
											"__type" : "uid",
											"uidString" : "ssfOpVuPScChGInaRsDk0w=="
										},
										"paragraphStyle" : {
											"__type" : "textStyle"
										},
										"string" : "Might just become:\nAsset\nLiability\nEquity\nIncome\nExpense (need to distinguish between Goods, Services, Insurance?)\n\nOptionally might include:\nTaxes and Government Charges\nGifts and Transfers\nInterest and Financing Costs\nDepreciation and Amortization"
									},
									{
										"__type" : "textSnippet",
										"children" : {
											"__type" : "snippets",
											"items" : [ ]
										},
										"createEmail" : {
											"__type" : "email",
											"emailString" : "<unknown>"
										},
										"createTime" : {
											"__type" : "time",
											"time" : {
												"__type" : "dateAndTime",
												"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T21:53:25.090857-04:00"
											}
										},
										"editEmail" : {
											"__type" : "email",
											"emailString" : "<unknown>"
										},
										"editTime" : {
											"__type" : "time",
											"time" : {
												"__type" : "dateAndTime",
												"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T21:53:45.308585-04:00"
											}
										},
										"uid" : {
											"__type" : "uid",
											"uidString" : "5ew3lLBmQMOIvN7DlLuJ5w=="
										},
										"paragraphStyle" : {
											"__type" : "textStyle"
										},
										"string" : "If Atlassian instead billed a material annual amount in advance, the accounting might become:\nAt payment:\n    Debit:  Prepaid Access **TODO: this was not on original list**\n    Credit: Amex\n\nEach month:\n    Debit:  Expense\n    Credit: Prepaid Access"
									}
								]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:43:24.511217-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:43:24.511217-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "Q3RyvXc9S9Ke3UK/fu5Raw=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "Nominal accounts"
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:42:29.628192-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:43:33.89723-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "ygO8lv8HSGSv21/S37qqGA=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "Balance sheet accounts would remain fairly traditional because these already cleanly represent financial entities like bank accounts, credit cards, mortages, etc."
						}
					]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:16:52.680798-04:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T12:02:02.203048-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "Bp4w0WlgRt24Wmml2tOmMw=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "We propose a more radical transformation: use accounts to represent financial concerns only i.e. posting/ledger behavior. Expenses might be the only expense account.\n\n\"Where\", you ask, rightly outraged, \"will I specify that a transaction is related to Education or Entertainment, so that I can budget and monitor spending as any financially responsible individual must?!\"\n\nThe answer is obvious once we realize that we are not building a multidimensional accounting application; we are unleashing financial and bookkeeping objects into the live, dynamic, rich world of Dynabook objects. Anything one might try to pigeonhole into an accounting dimension - projects, people, events, inventory - is appropriately modeled where it belongs (a project list, address book, calendar - and linked to the relevant transactions."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:46:57.723124-04:00"
								}
							},
							"editEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"editTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:46:57.723124-04:00"
								}
							},
							"uid" : {
								"__type" : "uid",
								"uidString" : "kgMfcHbdQXqUN4GeBJPOqQ=="
							},
							"paragraphStyle" : {
								"__type" : "textStyle"
							},
							"string" : "The value dimension might know how to:\nfind postings directly associated with a PpValue;\ntraverse descendants in the value DAG;\ndistinguish direct from inherited associations;\nroll amounts up through multiple parents;\ndisclose overlap;\napply an allocation policy."
						},
						{
							"__type" : "textSnippet",
							"children" : {
								"__type" : "snippets",
								"items" : [ ]
							},
							"createEmail" : {
								"__type" : "email",
								"emailString" : "<unknown>"
							},
							"createTime" : {
								"__type" : "time",
								"time" : {
									"__type" : "dateAndTime",
									"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-07-22T11:47:07.605908-04:00"
								}
